{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839002413,"sessionID":"ses_287c1c829ffeOktueOiT2J53jF","part":{"id":"prt_d783e552600190WFdr630SyINE","messageID":"msg_d783e46650019axScJYQCKIKWb","sessionID":"ses_287c1c829ffeOktueOiT2J53jF","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_c1f39c3c2df74d5c8dff93ea","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore AgentCube picod module","prompt":"Explore the AgentCube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand the pkg/picod module and related code. I need to write a design.md for \"AR-015 ŌĆö PicoD ÕæĮõ╗żµē¦ĶĪī API\".\n\nPlease find and read:\n1. Any existing pkg/picod directory and its contents\n2. The AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter type definitions (look in pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/)\n3. Any existing deployment or controller code that uses the client-go library\n4. The project's overall structure (top-level directories)\n5. Any existing design documents or architecture docs\n6. How commands are currently executed in the project (look for exec, command, run patterns)\n7. The deployment/ directory structure and any existing docs there\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- The pkg/picod module structure (if it exists) or where it should be created\n- The AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD type definitions (fields, spec, status)\n- Existing patterns for API design in the project\n- How the client-go generated code is used elsewhere\n- Any relevant constants, types, or interfaces that would be needed\n- The project's Go module path and dependencies","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_287c19288ffe2au17Nwsagz04v (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire AgentCube project. Here is the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Analysis for AR-015 -- PicoD Command Execution API\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**AgentCube** is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents, developed under `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`. The project was reverse-engineered from the source at `https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube` and the specifications were generated via SDD (Specification-Driven Development).\n\n**Go module path:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`  \n**Go version:** `1.24.4` (toolchain `go1.24.9`)\n\n### 2. The `pkg/picod` Module -- DOES NOT EXIST YET\n\nThe `pkg/picod` directory **does not exist** in the current workspace. However, it is thoroughly documented in the specs as a reverse-engineered module from the reference source at `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. The specs contain enough detail to reconstruct the entire module.\n\n**Where it should be created:**\n- `pkg/picod/` -- the main library package\n- `cmd/picod/` -- the binary entrypoint\n\n**Expected file structure** (inferred from the design doc):\n```\npkg/picod/\n  server.go        -- Server struct, Config, NewServer(), Run(), route registration\n  execute.go       -- ExecuteHandler, ExecuteRequest, ExecuteResponse, TimeoutExitCode=124\n  files.go         -- UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler, FileEntry, etc.\n  auth.go          -- AuthManager, AuthMiddleware, LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, MaxBodySize, PublicKeyEnvVar\n  health.go        -- HealthCheckHandler\ncmd/picod/\n  main.go          -- CLI flags (-port, -workspace), klog.InitFlags, server bootstrap\n```\n\n### 3. AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD Type Definitions\n\n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n**Version:** `v1alpha1`  \n**Package:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n\n#### AgentRuntime\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort         `json:\"targetPort\"`\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate     `json:\"podTemplate\"`              // Required\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration     `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`  // Default \"15m\"\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration     `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"` // Default \"8h\"\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels      map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    Spec        corev1.PodSpec    `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CodeInterpreter\n\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n    metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort                    `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate `json:\"template\"`              // Required\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration                `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\"`  // Default \"15m\"\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration                `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\"` // Default \"8h\"\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32                          `json:\"warmPoolSize,omitempty\"`\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType                    `json:\"authMode,omitempty\"`  // Default \"picod\", Enum: picod|none\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n    Ready      bool               `json:\"ready,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct {\n    Labels           map[string]string               `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n    Annotations      map[string]string               `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n    RuntimeClassName *string                         `json:\"runtimeClassName,omitempty\"`\n    Image            string                          `json:\"image,omitempty\"`\n    ImagePullPolicy  corev1.PullPolicy               `json:\"imagePullPolicy,omitempty\"`\n    ImagePullSecrets []corev1.LocalObjectReference   `json:\"imagePullSecrets,omitempty\"`\n    Environment      []corev1.EnvVar                 `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n    Command          []string                        `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n    Args             []string                        `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n    Resources        corev1.ResourceRequirements     `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Shared Types\n\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string       `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n    Name       string       `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Port       uint32       `json:\"port\"`\n    Protocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"` // Default \"HTTP\", Enum: HTTP|HTTPS\n}\n\ntype AuthModeType string\nconst (\n    AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n    AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n)\n\ntype ProtocolType string\nconst (\n    ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n    ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n)\n```\n\n### 4. PicoD Module Details (from `specs/code-execution/design.md`)\n\n#### Server Configuration\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int    `json:\"port\"`\n    Workspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### CLI Flags\n| Flag | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `-port` | `int` | `8080` |\n| `-workspace` | `string` | `\"\"` (resolves to CWD) |\n\n#### Environment Variables\n| Name | Constant | Usage |\n|------|----------|-------|\n| `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | PEM-encoded RSA public key (required, fatal if missing) |\n\n#### Constants\n| Name | Value | File |\n|------|-------|------|\n| `TimeoutExitCode` | `124` | `execute.go` |\n| `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` |\n| `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` |\n| `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` |\n| Default execute timeout | `60 * time.Second` | `execute.go` |\n| Default file mode | `0644` | `files.go` |\n| Dir creation mode | `0755` | `files.go` |\n\n#### Request/Response Structs\n\n**Execute:**\n```go\ntype ExecuteRequest struct {\n    Command    []string          `json:\"command\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Timeout    string            `json:\"timeout\"`\n    WorkingDir string            `json:\"working_dir\"`\n    Env        map[string]string `json:\"env\"`\n}\n\ntype ExecuteResponse struct {\n    Stdout    string    `json:\"stdout\"`\n    Stderr    string    `json:\"stderr\"`\n    ExitCode  int       `json:\"exit_code\"`\n    Duration  float64   `json:\"duration\"`\n    StartTime time.Time `json:\"start_time\"`\n    EndTime   time.Time `json:\"end_time\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Files:**\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n}\n\ntype UploadFileRequest struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"`\n    Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`\n}\n\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"`\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`\n}\n\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### Routes\n```go\napi := engine.Group(\"/api\")\napi.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n{\n    api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n    api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n    api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n    api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n}\nengine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n```\n\n#### Auth (JWT RS256)\n- `AuthManager` holds `*rsa.PublicKey` with `sync.RWMutex`\n- Middleware requires `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- JWT parsed with `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n- Only RSA signing methods accepted (HS256 rejected)\n- After validation, request body wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` at 32 MiB\n\n#### Path Security (`sanitizePath`)\n- Resolves symlinks in workspace directory\n- Strips leading `/` from absolute paths\n- Uses `filepath.Rel` to verify path is inside workspace\n- Double-checks after symlink resolution for final path\n\n### 5. Existing API Design Patterns in the Project\n\n**HTTP Framework:** Gin (Go) for all Go services (Workload Manager, Router, PicoD)\n\n**Workload Manager API patterns** (`pkg/workloadmanager`):\n| Method | Path | Auth | Handler |\n|--------|------|------|---------|\n| GET | `/health` | No | `handleHealth` |\n| POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | Conditional | `handleAgentRuntimeCreate` |\n| DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId` | Conditional | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n| POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Conditional | `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n| DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId` | Conditional | `handleDeleteSandbox` |\n\n**Router API patterns** (`pkg/router`):\n| Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n|--------|------|------------|---------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` |\n| GET/POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | Logger, Recovery, ConcurrencyLimit | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| GET/POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | same | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n\n**Error response patterns:**\n- Gin `gin.H{\"error\": string, \"code\": int}` for generic errors\n- Gin `gin.H{\"error\": string, \"code\": int, \"detail\": string}` for auth errors\n- `ErrorResponse{Message string}` for Workload Manager\n\n### 6. Client-Go Generated Code Usage\n\n**Module path:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`  \n**Generated by:** `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 via `hack/update-codegen.sh`\n\n**Key components:**\n- **Clientset:** `clientset/versioned.Interface` with `RuntimeV1alpha1()` accessor\n- **Typed clients:** `AgentRuntimeInterface`, `CodeInterpreterInterface` (CRUD: Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/Get/List/Watch/Patch)\n- **Informers:** `SharedInformerFactory` -> `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()` / `CodeInterpreters()`\n- **Listers:** `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister` with namespace-scoped sub-listers\n- **Fakes:** `clientset/versioned/fake/` for testing\n\n**Usage pattern** (from sandbox creation processor):\n```go\n// Get from informer cache (read-only, fast)\nruntime, err := informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().\n    Lister().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n\n// For creation of external CRDs (Sandbox/SandboxClaim), use dynamic client\ndynamicClient.Resource(SandboxGVR).Namespace(ns).Create(ctx, sandbox, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n```\n\n**Regeneration:** `make gen-client` -> `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`\n\n### 7. Key Dependencies (from `go.mod`)\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec`, etc. |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.*`, `schema.*`, `runtime.*` |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | `v2.130.1` | Logging |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | `v1.10.0` | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | `v5.2.2` | JWT RS256 |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | `v9.17.1` | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | `v1.0.69` | Valkey client |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | Scheme builder, reconciler |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` | `v0.1.1` | Sandbox CRD types |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | `v1.6.0` | UUID generation |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | `v1.11.1` | Testing |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | `v2.35.0` | Redis testing |\n\n### 8. Key Constants and Interfaces Used Across the Project\n\n**Common types** (`pkg/common/types`):\n```go\nconst (\n    AgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n    CodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n    SandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n    SandboxClaimsKind   = \"SandboxClaim\"\n)\n```\n\n**GVR variables** (`pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go`):\n```go\nAgentRuntimeGVR    = {Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"}\nCodeInterpreterGVR = {Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"}\nSandboxGVR         = {Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxes\"}\nSandboxClaimGVR    = {Group: \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"sandboxclaims\"}\n```\n\n**Label/Annotation keys:**\n```go\nSessionIdLabelKey         = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\nWorkloadNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\nSandboxNameLabelKey       = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\nLastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"\nIdleTimeoutAnnotationKey  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n```\n\n**Identity secret** (for PicoD JWT):\n```go\nIdentitySecretName      = \"picod-router-identity\"\nPublicKeyDataKey        = \"public.pem\"\nPrivateKeyDataKey       = \"private.pem\"\nIdentitySecretNamespace = \"default\"  // overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env\n```\n\n**Store interface** (`pkg/store`):\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### 9. Project Architecture Summary\n\n```\nClient / SDK / CLI\n  -> Router (Deployment :8080, pkg/router)\n     <-> Redis/Valkey (session store, pkg/store)\n     -> WorkloadManager (Service :8080, pkg/workloadmanager)\n        <-> Redis/Valkey\n        -> K8s API: CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n  Sandbox Pods (with PicoD daemon inside, pkg/picod)\n  Agentd (idle cleanup controller, pkg/agentd)\n  Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n```\n\n### 10. Existing Design Documents Available\n\nAll design docs are in `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/`:\n- `specs/code-execution/design.md` -- **PicoD design (most relevant for AR-015)**\n- `specs/code-execution/spec.md` -- PicoD specification with scenarios\n- `specs/sandbox-orchestration/design.md` -- CRD types, Workload Manager, client-go usage\n- `specs/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/design.md` -- Sandbox creation flow\n- `specs/session-routing/design.md` -- Router design, JWT generation, reverse proxy\n- `specs/session-store/design.md` -- Redis/Valkey store design\n- `specs/idle-cleanup/design.md` -- Agentd idle cleanup reconciler\n- `specs/deployment/design.md` -- Helm chart, Dockerfiles, Makefile, RBAC\n- `specs/deployment/client-go.md` -- Full client-go generated code reference\n- `specs/python-sdk/design.md` -- Python SDK design\n- `specs/cli-toolkit/design.md` -- CLI toolkit design\n- `specs/integrations/design.md` -- Dify plugin and PCAP analyzer\n\n### 11. Key Insights for Writing AR-015 Design\n\nFor \"AR-015 -- PicoD Command Execution API\", you have exhaustive source material in:\n1. **`specs/code-execution/design.md`** (245 lines) -- exact Go structs, constants, route registration, auth middleware, path sanitization, HTTP error shapes, server initialization, health response, and HTTP server configuration\n2. **`specs/code-execution/spec.md`** (179 lines) -- full requirement/specification with Given/When/Then scenarios for execute, file upload, file listing, file download, health, and JWT auth\n\nThe PicoD module uses **Gin** in **ReleaseMode**, with **JWT RS256** authentication via an RSA public key loaded from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable. The command execution uses `exec.CommandContext` with configurable timeouts (default 60s), and the timeout exit code is `124`. File operations support both multipart form-data and JSON Base64 uploads, with path traversal protection via the `sanitizePath` function.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_287c19288ffe2au17Nwsagz04v","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore AgentCube picod module","time":{"start":1775838850420,"end":1775839002410}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775839002463,"sessionID":"ses_287c1c829ffeOktueOiT2J53jF","part":{"id":"prt_d7840bf2c001Hsze6NZvW2ADxP","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d783e46650019axScJYQCKIKWb","sessionID":"ses_287c1c829ffeOktueOiT2J53jF","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19674,"input":19256,"output":311,"reasoning":107,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.006004774}}
